&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s Degree&amp;nbsp;in Mathematics, Statistics, Actuarial Science, Finance, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Years of Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ year of relevant experience&amp;nbsp;of actuarial experience, with prior exposure to ALM, actuarial modeling software, and asset modeling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with life and annuity products, general account assets, and actuarial projection methodologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;License/Certification&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
