&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Investments Analyst will support the Enterprise Investments vertical in managing critical front-office functions across F&amp;amp;G&#39;s investment business. This position will provide essential operational and analytical support for strategic asset allocation projects, investment manager due diligence and onboarding, cash management, investment reporting, and cross-functional coordination. The role reports to the Manager, Investments and has no subordinates. This position will interact regularly with members of the Investments department, Treasury, Actuarial, Investment Accounting, external asset managers, and senior leadership.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the investment opportunity and/or manager evaluation and selection process, including coordinating due diligence workflows and maintaining documentation
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in developing and maintaining quantitative frameworks for comparing investment managers and strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct relative value analysis among multiple investment opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare meeting agendas and take detailed notes during manager meetings and presentations&lt;/li&gt;
